.TH "LIGHTNING-REQ" 1 "June 2026" "lightning 0.6.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-req \- request payments (invoice, offer, decode, QR)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning req invoice
[\fIargs\fR]
.br
.B lightning req offer
[\fIargs\fR]
.br
.B lightning req decode
\fI<string>\fR
.br
.B lightning req qr
\fI<text>\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Create and manage incoming payment requests.
.TP
.B req invoice [args]
BOLT-11 invoice management: create, list, cancel, status, decode.
Delegates to the \fBinvoice\fR subcommand dispatcher.
.TP
.B req offer [args]
BOLT-12 reusable offer management: create, pay.
A single offer string can be paid many times.
.TP
.B req decode <string>
Detect and decode any Lightning string: BOLT-11 invoice, BOLT-12 offer,
LNURL (bech32), or Lightning Address (user@domain).
.TP
.B req qr <text>
Render a string as a QR code (ANSI terminal output by default;
\fB--png\fR/\fB--svg\fR write to a file).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1),
.BR lightning-pay (1),
.BR lightning-invoice (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
